<h4>Tenor Juan Spiwak</h4>
<article class="collapsible-content" style="display: block;">
  <p style="text-align: justify">
    On several websites we can find information that the excellent tenor Juan Spiwak (also Spivak and Spiwack) was born in Slovenia. This is probably not true, in all probability he was born in Philadelphia (USA) to Russian parents of Jewish descent, and spent his childhood in Odessa with his grandparents. He first worked in Vienna and then all over Germany, most recently in Berlin. Due to the political situation, he immigrated to America, where he re-applied for American citizenship. More information at: <a href="http://www.historicaltenors.net/english/spivak.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">historicaltenors.net</a>.
    His recordings are excellent, I definitely recommend listening - here is a duet from Richard Wagner's Lohengrin opera with Czech-Austrian soprano Mario Jeritzo.
